{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17515166","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17515166"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T13:29:54+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T13:29:54+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12416"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"12416","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/12416"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.45,0.13,0.17,0.03,0.22]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4924"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"100096"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"4924","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4924"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question","status":"accepted","createdAt":"2023-01-27T02:39:26+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-04-24T09:44:15+09:30","updatedAction":"commented","acceptedAt":"2023-08-14T16:04:27+09:30","editorNotifiedAt":null,"feedbackAt":"2025-09-25 12:11:44"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12416"}},"updatedBy":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"16432"}},"author":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"6927"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"82488"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"10"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"697"},{"type":"tags","id":"1027"},{"type":"tags","id":"4971"},{"type":"tags","id":"11632"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"8052"},{"type":"contributions","id":"8399"},{"type":"contributions","id":"8786"},{"type":"contributions","id":"9239"},{"type":"contributions","id":"14121"},{"type":"contributions","id":"14579"},{"type":"contributions","id":"15414"},{"type":"contributions","id":"15979"},{"type":"contributions","id":"32987"},{"type":"contributions","id":"32989"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42754"}]},"lastContribution":{"data":null},"lastRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"82488"}},"lastActivity":{"data":null},"lastFeedback":{"data":null}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"100096","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/100096"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 35-year-old woman presents to a metropolitan General Practice clinic for a mental health review. She has a medical history of persistent depressive disorder and borderline personality disorder, with chronic suicidal ideation but no specific intent or plans. She has had brief crisis admissions to hospital in the past. Discharge summaries indicate consistent diagnoses and brief assessments. She has tried multiple antidepressants with little mood improvement and has a history of non-adherence to pharmacotherapy. She does not take any regular medications.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, she appears distressed. Her vital signs are within normal limits. She expresses a desire to end her life but has no active plans. She reports a history of physical and emotional abuse by her current partner, feeling trapped in an unsafe environment, though there has been no recent domestic violence. She is unemployed, lacks a support system, and has two children. She expresses worry about leaving her children behind. She does not consent to inpatient management.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate next step in management?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Provide weekly psychotherapy and refer for psychiatrist assessment and management","Arrange for immediate hospitalisation against the patient\u0027s will","Provide the patient with information on local support services and helplines","Prescribe fluoxetine and schedule frequent GP reviews","Contact child protective services to ensure the safety of the patient\u0027s children"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with a complex psychiatric history including persistent depressive disorder, borderline personality disorder, and chronic suicidal ideation. The most appropriate next step is to \u003Cstrong\u003Eprovide weekly psychotherapy and refer for psychiatrist assessment and management\u003C/strong\u003E. This ensures immediate support and facilitates a comprehensive, multidisciplinary approach, which is essential for complex cases involving chronic suicidality and comorbid personality disorder.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EArrange for immediate hospitalisation against the patient\u0027s will\u003C/strong\u003E is not appropriate here, as involuntary admission is reserved for situations where there is an immediate risk to safety or loss of capacity. The patient has no active plans and retains decision-making capacity, so hospitalisation against her wishes is not justified and may be counterproductive.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProvide the patient with information on local support services and helplines\u003C/strong\u003E is insufficient as a sole intervention given the severity and chronicity of her symptoms. While these resources are valuable, they do not replace the need for structured, ongoing professional support and psychiatric input.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPrescribe fluoxetine and schedule frequent GP reviews\u003C/strong\u003E is not the best option, as the patient has already trialled multiple antidepressants with little benefit and has a history of non-adherence. Addressing her complex needs requires more than a change in medication and routine follow-up.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EContact child protective services to ensure the safety of the patient\u0027s children\u003C/strong\u003E is not warranted at this stage, as there is no evidence of immediate risk to the children. This action may be considered if concerns about child safety arise, but the current priority is to address the patient\u0027s mental health and social circumstances through a coordinated care plan.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe optimal approach involves a multidisciplinary team, including regular counselling, psychiatric evaluation and management, social work, and domestic violence services. It is important to consider the local context, as resource availability may affect which services can be accessed. A multidisciplinary strategy addresses the patient\u0027s complex needs, including her mental health, social circumstances, and safety concerns. Regular General Practice reviews should also be included in this integrated care plan to monitor progress and adjust interventions as needed.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Referral to a psychiatrist and provision of regular psychotherapy is essential for complex cases involving chronic suicidality and comorbid personality disorder.","Involuntary hospitalisation is reserved for situations where there is immediate risk to safety or loss of capacity.","A multidisciplinary approach, including social and domestic violence support, is critical in managing complex psychiatric presentations."],"references":["Australian Medical Association. Code of Ethics [Internet]. 2004 [cited 2023 01 26]. Available from: https://www.ama.com.au/articles/code-ethics-2004-editorially-revised-2006-revised-2016","Webb B, Looi JC, Allison S, Nance M, Dhillon R, Bastiampillai T. A proposed clinical pathway for the patients with Borderline Personality Disorder presenting to Emergency Departments. Australasian Psychiatry. 2023;31(4):458-462. Available at: https://journals.sagepub.com/doi/10.1177/10398562231167976?icid=int.sj-abstract.citing-articles.3","Singleton G, Beatson J, Rao S. Providing effective treatment for borderline personality disorder. Aust J Gen Pract. 2025 Mar;54(3):112-116. doi: 10.31128/AJGP-11-23-7031. PMID: 40043287."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"82488"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12416"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"82488","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/82488"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-04-24T09:43:42+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-04-24T09:44:51+09:30","number":26,"notes":"","plagiarismCheckedAt":"2025-04-24T09:43:48+09:30","plagiarismScore":0,"plagiarismReportUrl":"https://emedici-copyleaks.syd1.digitaloceanspaces.com/plagiarism-report-4924-26.pdf?X-Amz-Content-Sha256=UNSIGNED-PAYLOAD\u0026X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256\u0026X-Amz-Credential=DO00QAKVE68N83EBLT2J%2F20250929%2Fsyd1%2Fs3%2Faws4_request\u0026X-Amz-Date=20250929T035956Z\u0026X-Amz-SignedHeaders=host\u0026X-Amz-Expires=601200\u0026X-Amz-Signature=e0579d6c3e3c511773520f18328c4684bb77a8e3f937f35773051729f4cb8719"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4924"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"100096"}},"author":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"16432"}},"generation":{"data":null}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"10","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/10"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udfad","name":"Psychiatry","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:46+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"66","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/66"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Management","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"72","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/72"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Graduating","s